annotationA: 2-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)histidine synthase subunit 2; Required for the first step in the synthesis of diphthamide, a post-translational modification of histidine which occurs in translation elongation factor 2
annotationB: Diphthamide methyltransferase; Diphthine synthase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: peptidyl-diphthamide biosynthetic process from peptidyl-histidine
